---
description: Enforce pnpm as the only package manager for agent commands
alwaysApply: true
---

When working with this repository, use `pnpm` only for package and script commands.

Rules:
- Always use `pnpm` equivalents instead of `npm`, `yarn`, or `bun`.
- Use `pnpm install` for dependency installation.
- Use `pnpm add` / `pnpm remove` for dependency changes.
- Use `pnpm run <script>` or `pnpm <script>` for scripts.
- Never suggest or execute `npm`, `npx`, `yarn`, or `bun` commands unless the user explicitly asks for them.
